  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen Women and PWDs Participation in Local Governance.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development of Information, Education and Communication (IE&amp;C) materials.
Stakeholders consultation meetings
Development of Information, Education and Communication (IE&amp;C) materials.
Sensitization and awareness creation
Capacity building and empowerment
Community radio and information centers with phone-in segments
Focus Group Discussions
Communities interface forums 
 Stakeholders review meetings 
Monitoring and Evaluation</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to increase voice, inclusive, and participation of women and people with disabilities in local governance. 
This project also seeks to contribute to achieving increased accountability and responsiveness of government at community and district levels to citizens especially women, children, young people and people with disabilities (PWDs).
In addition, this project seeks to contribute to achieving Goal 4 of the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals: Achieve Gender Equality, Social Inclusion and Human Rights for all, which aims to bring about transformative change within societies, institutions and economic structures to end gender inequality and all other forms of discrimination impacting on participation in social, political and economic life.</narrative>
  </description>
